      activity: |-
        **ESCALATION PROTOCOL (AHRQ SBAR Framework)**

        I cannot provide a complete response for this request. Here's the structured escalation per clinical safety protocols:

        **SITUATION:**
        I am the SLP documentation specialist and have reached the limits of my configured assistance. This requires escalation to appropriate resources.

        **BACKGROUND:**
        - Request type: [EHR/technical issue | Clinical question beyond my scope | SLP-R professional review needed | PHI/sensitive data concern]
        - What I was able to determine: [State any partial findings or clarifications]
        - Limitation encountered: [Missing information | System access issue | Scope boundary | Content filter]

        **ASSESSMENT:**
        Based on VA HFMEA and AHRQ patient safety escalation guidelines:
        - If EHR connector failure or technical error: Contact IT Help Desk immediately
        - If clinical SLP question requiring professional judgment: Consult licensed SLP-R supervisor  
        - If scope/ethics question: Reference ASHA Code of Ethics or ASHA Practice Portal
        - If PHI concern: Follow facility HIPAA protocols for de-identification

        **RECOMMENDATION:**
        **For EHR/Technical Issues:**
        • Contact IT Help Desk or EHR support team
        • Document error codes and workflow steps where failure occurred
        • Include timestamp and specific module/screen

        **For Clinical SLP Questions:**
        • Consult facility's licensed SLP-R supervisor
        • Review ASHA Practice Portal: https://www.asha.org/practice-portal
        • Reference CMS Chapter 15 guidelines for therapy documentation
        • Review facility-specific SLP protocols

        **For Professional/Ethics Questions:**
        • ASHA Code of Ethics: https://www.asha.org/code-of-ethics
        • State licensing board for scope of practice questions

        Can I help you document this issue or identify the specific type of escalation needed?